cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.AI

This paper deals with numerical methods and algorithms for large-scale datasets, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of numerical analysis (cs.NA), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) and its approximation using sketching, which is a common technique in numerical analysis and machine learning. The application of sketched SVD to Leverage Score Ordering is also relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NA and cs.LG, followed by cs.DS, cs.CV, and cs.AI.
